{
  "texts": [
    "This design included across-subject and within-subject variations in the treatment conditions; it did not allow within-case-subject comparisons because a case was encountered only once for a radiologist 38.",
    "Order effects were mitigated by the randomization of treatment conditions.",
    "The repeated-measure design included 33 radiologists in a repeated-measure setup (Supplementary Fig. 2).",
    "Each radiologist read a total of 60 patient cases, each under each of the four treatment conditions and producing a total of 240 diagnoses.",
    "The radiologist completed the experiment in four sessions, and the radiologist read the same 60 randomly selected patient cases in each session under each of the various treatment arms."
  ]
}